title: Automatic translation device
description:
Automatic translation device technology allows a player to understand alien words more quickly, even though you haven't learned them yet.

It records and parses nearby conversations before running the data through a contextual learning system to determine intended meaning.

During a conversation, you will see more words of the conversation than you have actually learned. Even if you have only learned a couple of words, more of the sentence will be understandable. However, the translator doesn't teach you these additional words - they are only understood for the duration of the conversation (or if the same line is repeated by that character within a short time by talking to them again).

title: Exosuit Upgrade Station
description:
The Exosuit Upgrade Station is a static terminal found:
* On Space Stations, to the left side of the interior (opposite the appearance modifier), near the Exosuit merchant.
* On the Space Anomaly, directly across from the Exosuit vendor Ena Zuzzi, between the Starship and Multi-Tool research areas.

It features a holographic display of an exosuit and a small interface panel.

Each time the station is used, the Traveller may purchase one new inventory slot for Units. The location of the unlocked slot (General, Technology, or Cargo tab) may be selected manually.

The cost of the upgrade increases with each slot purchased, scaling progressively higher:
* General inventory slots start cheap and become more expensive with each upgrade.
* Technology and Cargo slots follow their own individual cost curves.

title: Multi-Tool
description:
thumb|The Waveform Focuser N56-P
The Multi-Tool is the general term used for the mining tool and weapon that every player possesses.

A Multi-Tool is (usually) shaped like a gun. They are a multifunctional device that can extract resources, scan / analyze and record fauna, flora and minerals, excavate terrain, and even eliminate obstacles and disturbances (using the latter function). 

However, if you don't install each technology (or repair tech slots if broken, in the case of found Multi-Tools, rather than purchased ones), you won't be able to use each respective feature.

In most cases, especially early on, the only function available by default is the basic Mining Beam and melee attack, and possibly a single weapon type, the most common of which being the Boltcaster.

There are many functions that seem to have nothing to do with the multi-tool, but are actually related. For example, the Analysis Visor that provides the compass display at the top of the HUD is also effective only when it is installed in the multi-tool.

Depending on the setting, the player's hands will be extended or shown. Upon starting a new game, you might think of it as a little more than a makeshift dowsing rod, but you'll soon find that it's an important piece of equipment that will cover a large part of your activities while exploring on foot. Multi-tools will be an important part of the Journey, along with your Exosuit and Starships

The Waveform Focuser N56-P, which comes as a default in many game modes, has a small number of slots and is not suitable for versatility. It is recommended not to put up with the initial equipment for too long. Save up your money to buy something, or pick it up somewhere and grab some new equipment as soon as possible.

title: Multi-tool Weapons
description:
thumb|The Weapon Indicator
While the multi-tool has many functions, one of the primary functions is that of a weapon.

There are a variety of beams and projectiles which the Multi-tool can emit. They are often called "weapons". Only one weapon may be selected for use at a time. The selected weapon is displayed in the Weapon Indicator, which is part of the user interface while an avatar is on foot. It is found in the upper right corner of the screen, where there is a bar with two boxes beneath it. The Weapon Indicator itself is the box on the right and also includes the dots to the right of the box. The selected weapon is named in the box. The dots indicate how many weapons are installed and which number is selected.
